# Statistics Layout Alignment Plan

## Goal Description
The user wants to align the result values in the statistics section of the [Stats](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%8A%A4%EC%9C%84%EC%B9%98%EC%9B%B9%EC%84%9C%EB%B9%84%EC%8A%A4/daily-habit-tracker/src/Stats.jsx#4-77) page. Currently, the values might be misaligned visually. The goal is to ensure the numbers and labels in the statistics cards are properly centered and aligned.

## Proposed Changes

### CSS Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [App.css](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%8A%A4%EC%9C%84%EC%B9%98%EC%9B%B9%EC%84%9C%EB%B9%84%EC%8A%A4/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.css)
- Update `.stats-row` to use `display: flex` with `justify-content: space-around` or `space-between` to distribute items evenly.
- Update `.stat-item` to ensure text centering and proper padding.
- Ensure `.mini-stat-row` in the overview section aligns the text and the badge correctly, likely using `align-items: center` and `justify-content: space-between`.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  Navigate to the Statistics page (`/stats`).
2.  Observe the "Active Habits" and "Total Checks" cards. They should be evenly spaced and their content centered.
3.  Observe the "Overview" list. The habit name and frequency badge should be aligned on the same horizontal line, with the name on the left and badge on the right.
